1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
1
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
2
3 SENATE
3 RESOLUTION 26 By: Grellner
4
4
5
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
6
7 A Resolution supporting Senate Bill 1640; urging
7 expeditious committee and floor consideration; and
8 affirming the Senate’s commitment to enforcing its
8 rules and the Oklahoma Constitution by condemning
9 intoxication during session.
9
10
10
11
11
12 WHEREAS, Senate Rule 5-5 D. of the Standing Rules of the Senate
12
13 for the 60th Oklahoma Legislature (2025-2026) prohibits the
13
14 consumption of alcohol in the chamber and mandates removal by
14
15 security personnel of any member in an intoxicated state; and
15
16 WHEREAS, Article 2, Section 11 of the Oklahoma Constitution
16
17 declares that “Drunkenness and the excessive use of intoxicating
17
18 liquors while in office shall constitute sufficient cause for
18
19 impeachment or removal therefrom”; and
19
20 WHEREAS, incidents during the 2025 legislative session
20
21 highlighted apparent violations of these provisions, with no
21
22 enforcement action taken; and
22
23 WHEREAS, Senator Shane Jett has introduced Senate Bill 1640 to
23
24 strengthen prohibitions on alcohol consumption or possession by
24
Req. No. 3582 Page 1

1 lawm akers while on duty in the Capitol, including provisions for
1
2 Breathalyzer testing, escalating penalties (fines, expulsion,
2
3 mandatory treatment), ethics referrals, and accountability for
3
4 leadership failing to act; and
4
5 WHEREAS, swift passage of such measures would demonstrate the
5
6 Senate’s unwavering commitment to sobriety, accountability, and
6
7 adherence to its own rules and the Oklahoma Constitution.
7
8 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE 2ND SESSION
8
9 OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
9
10 THAT the Senate strongly supports Senate Bill 1640 as a
10
11 necessary step to reinforce existing rules and constitutional
11
12 standards prohibiting intoxication during official duties.
12
13 THAT the Senate urges the appropriate committee(s) to grant
13
14 Senate Bill 1640 a hearing at the earliest possible date, and calls
14
15 for expeditious floor consideration and passage to affirm that the
15
16 Oklahoma State Senate stands firmly by its rules and the Oklahoma
16
17 Constitution.
17
18 THAT the Senate condemns intoxication in the chamber during
18
19 session as incompatible with the dignity and responsibility of
19
20 legislative service and reaffirms its expectation of sober,
20
21 professional conduct by all members.
